The paper deals with statistical queries and adaptivity in data analysis, which are topics that are commonly studied in computer science. The use of a mechanism to charge a price for each query and collect additional samples suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The need to ensure statistical validity without assumptions on query generation suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the use of a mechanism to incentivize non-adaptive queries suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
